<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">LEARN TO TWIST (2 OR MORE SONGS AT ONCE)</b></font> - <small>Feyowyn, BristleBain</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    When you have more than 1 song that is useful in a fight you will want to learn to twist songs (play more then one song at a time). This is a very simple process that is easier to do than discribe. Keep you best 3 combat songs hot keyed. When you get ready for combat, start the first song. The instant you see the message of the songs effect (ie "your wounds begin to heal" or if you are real good at timing even a little before) press the hot key for the 2nd song. you will see the message " you stop singing" and your song icons will start to reappear. The instant the icon reappears, press the 2nd song key again and you will start to sing that song. When the the message for that song appears, restart the first song.  At this point you will notice you have 2 active song icons (buffs) on the top right of your screen. This is because most bard song effects last from 5 to 15 seconds. Thus even after you stop singing one song and start another, the effect will remain for a bit and you will have the benifit from both songs. By continueing to cycle between the songs in this manner you can keep 2 to three songs going at once. (I have heard some people can keep 4 songs going but this it beyond my abilities). With my whistling war song and heal song going, I can kill some yellow cons and only be down 2 bubbles of health.

Now you ask why do you only hot key 3 songs. That is a good question and shows you were paying attention. Use the other 3 spots to hot key a inventory slot and your weapon1 and weapon 2 slots. This will let you switch between weapons and instruments quickly. After you have made the hot keys, you will see you can move items around in the hot key spots just like you can with your inventory open but with out the time waste of switching to the inventory screen. To switch to an instrument when you have you weapon and shild on, first click on the weapon 1 slot. This will pick the weapon up with your curser. Now click on the instrument in your inventory slot. This will put the weapon in your inventory and pick up the instrument. Now click on the weapon 2 slot and you will put your instrument in the weapon 2 slot when you need it to get inproved song effects. The shield will be on your curser. That is not a problem. just leave it there until you want to switch back to weapon and shield. Then you reverse the process. Note, the order you do this in is important as it will not work out of sequence and it is much faster to do than to describe.
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
